Random Maps Roadmap
===================

Context
-------
Extend the current HTML tools UI and randomizer so the project can generate
randomized world maps while preserving a completable game. The system may
shuffle overworld sectors, towns, caves, and connector regions, but the final
layout must always keep a valid critical path from game start to final dungeon.

Goals
-----
- Allow seeded random map generation from the tools UI and CLI.
- Preserve all critical progression requirements: towns, quest items, keys,
  story flags, locked doors, dungeon access, and final-game routing.
- Guarantee spatial connectivity, not just abstract progression logic.
- Support dry-run preview, failure diagnostics, and repeatable seeds.
- Keep ROM/map data injection safe and compatible with existing build checks.

Quality Gates
-------------
- Every generated seed must pass both progression validation and spatial path
  validation.
- Dry-run generation must never modify ASM or map binaries.
- Applied map changes must still allow `cmd //c verify.bat` to pass after the
  final integration path is implemented.
- Generator output must be deterministic for the same seed and options.
- Failure output must explain which constraint blocked generation.

Phase 1 - Discovery and Constraint Inventory
--------------------------------------------

[todo][critical][RM-001] Build a complete world-progression inventory
Describe every critical location, town, cave, dungeon, quest trigger, key item,
locked door, and boss gate that participates in game completion.
Files: `tools/progression_validator.js`, `notes.txt`, `src/towndata.asm`,
`src/mapdata.asm`, `src/dungeon.asm`
Acceptance:
- A single source of truth lists all critical nodes and unlock conditions.
- Each node is tagged as required, optional, or cosmetic.

[todo][critical][RM-002] Inventory overworld and cave transition points
Catalogue all sector exits, cave entrances, town entrances, dungeon entrances,
stairs, one-way exits, and return points used by the game.
Files: `data/maps/`, `tools/map_viewer.js`, `tools/editor/map_editor.js`
Acceptance:
- Every transition has a stable identifier and source/target definition.
- One-way and special-case transitions are explicitly marked.

[todo][critical][RM-003] Define passability and traversal rules by tile type
Document which tiles are walkable, blocked, conditional, bridge-like, water,
mountain, indoor-only, or script-gated so pathfinding matches game behavior.
Files: `tools/map_viewer.js`, `tools/editor/map_editor.js`, `src/player.asm`,
`src/dungeon.asm`
Acceptance:
- A reusable rules module can answer whether a tile is traversable.
- Any assumptions that differ from live game logic are documented.

[todo][high][RM-004] Identify map randomization scope presets
Define supported modes such as sector shuffle only, critical-path-preserving
shuffle, entrance shuffle, and full generated layout with optional safeguards.
Files: `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`, `tool-ui-plan.json`
Acceptance:
- Presets are named, documented, and ordered from safest to wildest.
- Each preset lists exactly what may move and what must stay fixed.

[todo][high][RM-005] Record technical constraints for binary-safe map output
Determine which map assets can change freely, which require same-size RLE
output, and where direct binary replacement vs remap tables are safer.
Files: `tools/editor/map_editor.js`, `src/mapdata.asm`, `tools/inject_game_data.js`
Acceptance:
- The implementation path avoids accidental data shifts.
- The todo list names which assets can be patched in-place vs regenerated.

Phase 2 - Data Model and Validation Core
----------------------------------------

[done][critical][RM-006] Create a canonical map graph model
Represent the world as nodes and edges covering overworld sectors, interiors,
towns, caves, door locks, story gates, and entrance warps.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_graph.js` (new), `tools/progression_validator.js`
Acceptance:
- Graph data can be loaded from current assets without manual edits.
- Critical path nodes are addressable by stable IDs.

[done][critical][RM-007] Extend progression validation with spatial reachability
Upgrade the validator so it checks not only abstract stage order, but whether
the player can physically walk from reachable nodes to newly unlocked nodes.
Files: `tools/progression_validator.js`, `tools/randomizer/map_graph.js`
Acceptance:
- Validator fails if items/story logic pass but map routing is blocked.
- Output explains the first unreachable required milestone.
Note: Current implementation adds stage-aware overworld reachability milestones.
It still needs full cave/event/door-state modeling for complete quest accuracy.

[done][critical][RM-008] Build tile-level pathfinding helpers
Implement BFS/A* helpers that can evaluate passability inside sectors/rooms and
across entrance links to measure true traversable routes.
Files: `tools/randomizer/pathfinder.js` (new), `tools/map_viewer.js`
Acceptance:
- Helper can prove a path between two coordinates when one exists.
- Helper distinguishes unreachable, one-way, and gated paths.

[todo][high][RM-009] Add stage-aware world validation fixtures
Create fixtures for early, mid, and late-game states so the validator can test
movement using different item/flag sets.
Files: `tools/randomizer/testdata/` (new), `tools/progression_validator.js`
Acceptance:
- Fixtures cover at least start, Parma/Deepdale, Malaga/Stow, and endgame.
- Validation tests can run without editing live game assets.

[todo][high][RM-010] Create failure-reporting primitives for generation
Standardize error objects for disconnected graph, blocked entrance, impossible
door chain, unreachable key item, and seed exhaustion.
Files: `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`, `tools/randomizer/map_graph.js`
Acceptance:
- Generator failures produce machine-readable codes and human-readable messages.

Phase 3 - Randomization Design
------------------------------

[todo][critical][RM-011] Design the critical-path backbone algorithm
Define how required regions are ordered and connected before optional sectors
are placed, so the generator always builds a solvable backbone first.
Files: `tools/randomizer/` design docs, `tools/progression_validator.js`
Acceptance:
- The design guarantees a start-to-finish chain for all required milestones.
- Optional content cannot disconnect the backbone.

[todo][critical][RM-012] Design sector-edge compatibility rules
Specify which sector edges may connect based on terrain seams, bridges, town
entry placement, dungeon entrances, and intended traversal direction.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_constraints.js` (new), `data/maps/`
Acceptance:
- Illegal edge pairings are rejected before placement.
- Rules allow enough valid combinations for generation to succeed often.

[todo][critical][RM-013] Design entrance and exit remapping strategy
Plan how towns, caves, and dungeon entrances will be remapped when sectors or
rooms move, including paired return points and script-sensitive entrances.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_warps.js` (new), `src/towndata.asm`, `src/dungeon.asm`
Acceptance:
- Every moved entrance has a valid target and return mapping.
- Scripted entrances with special behavior are preserved or excluded.

[todo][high][RM-014] Decide how much terrain may be synthesized vs shuffled
Choose when to reuse existing sectors verbatim, when to rotate/mirror, and when
to generate connector tiles or bridge/path repairs.
Files: `tools/randomizer/`, `data/maps/`
Acceptance:
- The policy is explicit for each randomization preset.
- Any synthetic editing stays compatible with binary constraints.

[todo][high][RM-015] Define optional-content attachment rules
Place side caves, shops, dead ends, treasure routes, and non-critical flavor
areas as branches that never block or replace mandatory progression.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_constraints.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Optional placements enrich the map without consuming required slots.

Phase 4 - Generator Implementation
----------------------------------

[todo][critical][RM-016] Implement a seedable map RNG module
Add deterministic random helpers dedicated to map generation, separate from the
existing module randomizers so retries and previews stay reproducible.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_rng.js` (new), `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`
Acceptance:
- Same seed and options always produce identical placements.
- Retry logic derives deterministically from the main seed.

[todo][critical][RM-017] Implement backbone-first sector placement
Place required sectors/regions first using the designed progression chain, then
fill remaining slots with optional or cosmetic sectors.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Required milestones are placed before branch content.
- Placement fails fast when constraints cannot be satisfied.

[done][critical][RM-018] Implement connectivity-preserving shuffle mode
Create the first shippable mode that shuffles sectors around while preserving
all required connections and a valid playthrough.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Sectors can move to new coordinates.
- Generated layouts remain completable under validator checks.
Note: MVP implementation shuffles only overworld sectors without special tiles
and preserves reachability by matching boundary connectivity signatures against
the vanilla layout.

[done][critical][RM-019] Implement entrance remap generation
Generate the actual entrance/exit tables needed to keep towns, caves, and
dungeons aligned with their shuffled sector positions.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_warps.js` (new), `tools/inject_game_data.js`
Acceptance:
- Entering and exiting moved locations leads to the correct destinations.
- Return warps cannot strand the player.
Note: MVP exports remapped town teleport / Aries coordinates alongside moved
special-sector positions. Direct ASM injection for these runtime tables remains
to be wired.

[todo][high][RM-020] Implement connector repair rules
Where shuffled sectors create broken roads or impassable seams, apply minimal
tile edits to reconnect routes without redesigning the whole map.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_patcher.js` (new), `tools/editor/map_editor.js`
Acceptance:
- Repairs are minimal, deterministic, and validated by pathfinding.

[todo][high][RM-021] Support exclusion lists for fragile locations
Allow especially script-heavy or mechanically fragile sectors/rooms to stay
fixed until their relocation behavior is fully understood.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new), `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`
Acceptance:
- Exclusions are configurable by preset and visible in dry-run output.

[todo][medium][RM-022] Add controlled rotation/mirroring if viable
Evaluate whether safe sector transforms can increase variety without breaking
entrance coordinates, scripts, or passability assumptions.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new), `tools/randomizer/pathfinder.js`
Acceptance:
- Transforms are enabled only where validation proves them safe.

Phase 5 - ROM/Data Integration
------------------------------

[todo][critical][RM-023] Define map randomizer output format
Write a JSON schema or equivalent structure for placements, remaps, tile patch
operations, validation summaries, and metadata.
Files: `tools/data/random_maps.schema.json` (new), `tools/randomizer/`
Acceptance:
- Dry-run and applied runs both emit the same core structure.

[done][critical][RM-024] Implement asset export for randomized layouts
Serialize generated sector placements, entrance remaps, and tile patches to a
stable intermediate file that other tools and the UI can consume.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new), `tools/data/`
Acceptance:
- Output is seed-stable and diff-friendly.
Note: MVP now exports both a JSON manifest and generated sector binary assets
for overworld filler sectors.

[todo][critical][RM-025] Implement safe map injection path
Apply approved randomized map data back into the project without corrupting map
assets, warp data, or build output.
Files: `tools/inject_game_data.js`, `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Apply step updates only intended files.
- Resulting project still builds and verifies when integration is complete.

[todo][high][RM-026] Add rollback-friendly staging for applied maps
Write generated outputs to predictable files so a developer can inspect diffs,
reapply a seed, or discard generated artifacts cleanly.
Files: `tools/randomizer/`, `tools/data/`
Acceptance:
- Generated artifacts are easy to review before injection.

Phase 6 - CLI and Automation
----------------------------

[done][critical][RM-027] Add `maps` as a first-class randomizer module
Extend the unified randomizer CLI with a map flag, module wiring, seed string
support, dry-run behavior, and validation hooks.
Files: `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`
Acceptance:
- `maps` can be toggled independently or with presets.
- Seed strings encode whether map randomization was enabled.

[todo][critical][RM-028] Add map-specific CLI options
Expose preset, shuffle depth, repair policy, exclusions, retry budget, and
preview/export paths through CLI flags.
Files: `tools/randomizer/randomize.js`
Acceptance:
- Help text clearly documents map generation options.

[todo][high][RM-029] Add standalone map-randomizer dry-run command
Create a dedicated entry point for rapid iteration and debugging without running
every other randomizer module.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_randomizer.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Developers can preview layouts and diagnostics in one command.

[todo][high][RM-030] Add batch seed smoke-test automation
Run many seeds in dry-run mode and report pass/fail rates, common failure
reasons, and generation performance.
Files: `tools/randomizer/map_seed_audit.js` (new)
Acceptance:
- Batch runs identify unstable constraints before release.

Phase 7 - Tools UI Expansion
